-- Nikko Cordial Hires JPMorgan, Citigroup, UBS Analysts for Japan Equities
-- B y   T o s h i r o   H a s e g a w a
-- 2010-10-18T03:52:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/nikko-cordial-hires-jpmorgan-citigroup-ubs-analysts-for-japan-equities.html
Nikko Cordial Corp. , the investment
banking unit of Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc., said it
hired a total of three analysts from JPMorgan Chase & Co.,
Citigroup Inc. and UBS AG to cover Japanese companies.  Eiji Maeda , formerly a broadcast and amusement analyst at
JPMorgan Securities Japan Co.,  Taku Ouchi , who was an industrial
analyst at Citigroup Global Markets Japan Inc. and  Hiroharu Watanabe , who covered electronic parts at UBS Global Asset
Management (Japan) Ltd., joined Nikko today,  Kiyoo Kuniyoshi , a
spokesman for the brokerage said.  This brings the number of analysts at Nikko to 19, covering
a total of 15 sectors. Watanabe was a buy-side investor before
